The paper presents a meta-program that discovers compact theories from data, which involves combinatorics and algorithmic techniques. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the validation of candidate theories, which could fall under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The use of compactness as a metric to cut down the search space could also suggest the paper belongs to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on discovering theories from data could also suggest it belongs to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
